# FEDERATED TOTEM

The **Federated TOTEM** offers the barebones `TOTEM Image` service and the full-function 
service `DEBE Image` service as [docker images](https://www.docker.com/).  Because 
*Docker Images* are virtualized machines, service installation, administration,
security and accreditation are greatly simplified.  Both the
`TOTEM Image` and the `DEBE Image` services are networked with the `OS Image`, 
the `MySQL Image`, and (optionally) the `Neo4J Image`: after installation and startup, 
these images form a `TOTEM-MySQL-Neo4J-OS` or a `DEBE-MySQL-Ne04J-OS` network.

| Docker Image | Network Host | Provides | Requires Host |
| ----- | ------ | ----------- | -------- |
| OS  | totemhost | CentOS | none |
| MySQL | mysqlhost | MySQL database | none |
| Neo4J | neo4jhost | Optional Neo4J graphical database | none |
| TOTEM | totemhost | Barebones GUI-less web service | mysqlhost |
| DEBE  | totemhost | Full GUI web service | mysqlhost |

## Installation, Startup and Administration 

Download the [doc.sh](https://github.com/totemstan/dockify/raw/master/doc.sh) to 
your Linux system to install, startup and administrate these *Docker Images*:

	bash doc.sh IMAGE ACTION DB

After an *IMAGE* is *install*ed and *start*ed, it can *stop*ped, *admin*istered, 
*prime*d, *update*d, or *debug*ged.

Step 1. Install and start [Docker](https://www.docker.com/):

	bash doc.sh docker install
	bash doc.sh docker start

Step 2. Install **TOTEM** services:

	bash doc.sh os install
	bash doc.sh mysql install
	bash doc.sh neo4j install
	bash doc.sh totem install
	bash doc.sh debe install

Step 3: Start **TOTEM** databases:

	bash doc.sh mysql start
	bash doc.sh neo4j start

Step 4. Start your **TOTEM** service:

	bash doc.sh [debe | totem | docker] start

Step 5. Administrate a service:

	bash doc.sh [os | mysql | neo4j | debe | totem | docker] admin

